bio: <p>Victor Gaultney found his way to type through \
  dance, mathematics, music and calligraphy. A type \
  designer at SIL International since 1991, he develops \
  fonts for minority language groups around the world. \
  He holds an MA with distinction from the University \
  of Reading and returns regularly as a guest lecturer. \
  He is co-author of the SIL Open Font License and \
  works to bridge the gap between the typographic and \
  open source software communities. His most well-known \
  typeface - Gentium - has been a winner in two \
  international typeface design competitions and is \
  available under an open license.</p>